About washing

cashmere sweaters, dry clean them as much as possible. Washing instructions:
1. Water temperature is about 30C, use cashmere detergent, soak for 3 minutes
2. Gently pat and knead with hands and rinse with water for 3-4 times
3. Press the water out gently, or put it into the laundry bag and use the washing machine to dehydrate
4. Iron with low temperature steam and dry it in a cool place
About maintenance and storage

1. It is recommended to wear it every other day to restore the elasticity of the fiber and extend the life of the cashmere sweater
2. Fold the bag/box and lay it flat, and put the camphor ball into it to prevent insects (camphor ball cannot directly contact clothes)
About pilling

1. Slight pilling of cashmere sweater is normal
2. Pay attention to avoid friction with objects with rough surface when wearing at ordinary times
3. Pilling: use a professional hair remover

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings, help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyses reviews to verify trustworthiness.
